faq:
  - q: "What is a virtual executive assistant?"
    a: "A virtual executive assistant is a senior EA who supports founders and CEOs entirely remotely (calendar, inbox, board prep, project execution, vendor coordination) without physical office presence. The right virtual EA is indistinguishable from an in-office hire on output, often better on systems and documentation discipline because remote work forces it."
  - q: "How is a virtual EA different from a freelance VA?"
    a: "A freelance VA typically handles task-level work: data entry, scheduling, light research. A virtual EA operates at executive level: stakeholder coordination, board materials, decision logs, market entry, agent onboarding. The price difference reflects scope and seniority of decisions handled, not just hours."
  - q: "What tools do you work with?"
    a: "Standard stack: Google Workspace, Microsoft 365, Slack, Notion, Asana, ClickUp, Monday, HubSpot, Salesforce, Calendly, Loom, Zoom. I also build lightweight dashboards in Sheets/Excel when full CRM is overkill. Most engagements use the client's existing tools: I adapt, not impose."
  - q: "Do you sign NDAs?"
    a: "Yes, mutually. Standard mutual NDA before discovery, full engagement agreement before execution starts. Confidentiality is non-negotiable for executive-level work."
  - q: "How do you handle confidential information remotely?"
    a: "Encrypted-at-rest storage (1Password Business, Google Workspace with 2FA enforced), no personal email or phone for client work, client-owned shared drives for documents, signed NDA, and clear data retention rules at engagement end. I'm happy to work within your security policy if you have one."
